    "texts": [
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Identification features",
            "shortText": "<p>Chitons have eight dorsal shell plates surrounded by a soft fleshy girdle. Shell plates rectangular and flat with triangular anterior shell extensions and no insertion plates. Texture of shell unusual and characteristic, with longitudinal grooves and widely spaced out longitudinal rows of granules, some areas carrying radially-arranged granules. Girdle very narrow with needle-like, smooth spicules in chitinous cups; broad, small scales on the top, while the animal’s edge is surrounded with spicules. Underside with gills that extend from halfway along the animal to the anus. Colour white, red or orange.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_1_6225",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Adult size",
            "shortText": "<p>Small, typically around 10-15 mm total body length.&nbsp;</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_2_6226",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Distribution",
            "shortText": "<p><u>Global:</u> Endemic to South Africa.</p><p><u>Local/Regional:</u> Simon’s Town, Western Cape to Shelly Beach, KwaZulu-Natal.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_3_6227",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Biology",
            "shortText": "<p>Found in the intertidal zone solitary under stones.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_4_6228",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Food / prey",
            "shortText": "<p>Herbivorous - rasps algae off the rocks using its radula.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_5_6229",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Reproduction",
            "shortText": "<p>External fertilization, but in the pallial fold of the animal. Eggs hatch into juveniles brooded in the fold until big enough to be released.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_6_6230",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Similar species",
            "shortText": "<p>The wide and characteristically armored plates with longitudinal ridges and grooves, in combination with the very narrow girdle, easily identify this species. This is a rare species and the only one in the genus from the area. Other genus members of this occur in deep water.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_7_6231",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Further reading / References",
